![](https://images.squarespace-cdn.com/content/v1/5d56e145f80b7500016ba502/5d1d89a8-b363-4986-816f-dd9a453f8ae1/20250219_171159.jpg?format=original)

MJF and Hangman kickoff Dynamite talking about their prior history, with MJF originally having won the Dynamite Diamond Ring over Hangman.

Hangman says MJF has won so many things but he can't win the fans over. MJF cuts him off. He doesn't care about the fans.

He just wants to know where do they get off deciding who's actually a redeemable person. They won't forgive MJF but they forgive Hangman drinking blood, attacking veterans and burning down houses.

MJF says the fans forgave when Hangman took out the hasbeen Christopher Daniels. Hangman flips out. Don't you dare talk about Daniels. He went out fighting for his life. He died a warriors death.

He wouldn't have had it any other way. He was the best of us. Men like him made sure Hangman and MJF even had a place to wrestle today.

MJF could never understand that humility. He doesn't have the stomach for that selflessness.

MJF is a selfish coward. Hangman faces his problems head on. He runs from nothing and hides from nothing. He's worked for everything he's ever had.

And that's why the fans will accept Hangman after his villainy when they won't take MJF back.

Deep down MJF knows this.

MJF laughs. He asks if Hangman is a child because MJF doesn't care how he won. History books will remember him as a winner. He's earned everything.

MJF claims Hangman only got his accolades because he was the chosen one for AEW. All MJF needed was a scarf and a mic.

Hangman can be the main character all he wants. MJF spits in Hangman's face but they're not allowed to touch each other.

Hangman attacks security and only stops when Christopher Daniels gets in the ring. Daniels says this is what he was fighting to bring back. Don't listen to MJF, Daniels knows who Hangman is and Hangman knows who Hangman is.

What a segment 👏🏽👏🏽👏🏽👏🏽👏🏽

