![](https://images.squarespace-cdn.com/content/v1/5d56e145f80b7500016ba502/828a0f79-f3bd-4938-8690-961dfc7fd2f0/GkMblaiWcAApVHW.jpg?format=original)

The Opps def. The Patriarchy

Opps maintain a lot of control in this match, with Joe and Shibata tripping up Kip & Nick. Match ends when Nick Wayne gets caught in a REDRUM by Hook while Shibata keeps Sabian occupied and Samoa Joe prevents Christian Cage from returning to the ring to save his son!!!

![](https://images.squarespace-cdn.com/content/v1/5d56e145f80b7500016ba502/5e95d3b1-e92b-4bef-9530-8f2bda992d7a/GkMiRD_XQAEmDfk.jpg?format=original)

Powerhouse Hobbs def. Big Bill

Anything goes MEAT FIGHT... er, street fight! The crowd chants "MEAT FOREVER" as weapons are scattered all over the ring and ringside area.

Powerhouse Hobbs eventually SLAMS Big Bill through a pair of graffiti tagged, barbed wire tables which traps Big Bill and prevents him from answering the referees count of 10.

![](https://images.squarespace-cdn.com/content/v1/5d56e145f80b7500016ba502/234ac7f9-6882-4b03-a655-bf30578d57d5/GkMmMW5W0AEJ3_R.png?format=original)

  
Willow's interview with Renee gets interrupted when she gets jumped by Shafir. Most of the Death Riders emerge out by the ring where Jay White comes out onto the stage to confront them. PAC slowly creeps out to surround Jay White until Adam Copeland runs in from out of nowhere!!!

Copeland & Jay White get the upper hand and Cope grabs SPIKE. The Death Riders run off as Cope tells Mox his plan: to take down the Death Riders one-by-one until it's just Cope vs Mox at Revolution.

![](https://images.squarespace-cdn.com/content/v1/5d56e145f80b7500016ba502/5b36cd1f-37d1-4a50-baf7-e1f30d48d18c/GkMprcMWUAAhAlM.jpg?format=original)

Megan Bayne def. Kris Statlander

A battle between two of the strongest women in AEW. It’s a physical, back-and-forth bout as each woman gives it their all. Kris Statlander goes to the top rope, but Penelope Ford runs in and pushes Stat off of the corner.

Megan secures the victory and Penelope & Ford attack her after the match. Thunder Rosa runs in with a chair and after an awkward staredown, the women separate.

![](https://images.squarespace-cdn.com/content/v1/5d56e145f80b7500016ba502/999e3879-a411-4c89-9948-626a85448e13/GkMw4adbUAAwD-B.jpg?format=original)

 Orange Cassidy def. Roddy Strong

OC has earned the right to take on Takeshita for the International Title, a title OC is quite synonymous with. The Don Callis Family's Takeshita and Davis try to pummel OC into juice, but not until BATTLY CRY! blasts in the arena and Kenny Omega saves OC!

Takeshita leaves his title in the ring as Kenny grabs it and holds it up, looking Takeshita in the eyes. Kenny then realizes OC may also become the champion and the show closes with a staredown between Omega and OC